# Design: Baseline Test Debt Cleanup

## Technical Approach
Apply test-only remediations that align assertions and mocks with the current runtime contracts already enforced by the application. No production classes, configs, or runtime wiring will be modified. The implementation follows the proposal/spec boundaries: (1) security expectation alignment, (2) audit dependency mocking for MVC context, and (3) frontend flag mock-shape hardening.

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Options Considered | Tradeoff | Decision |
|---|---|---|---|
| Security expectation in admin MVC test | Keep `401` assertion; change to current observed security-layer rejection | Keeping `401` causes false failures; changing assertion may be misread as behavior change | Update test assertion to match current security middleware precedence (CSRF/auth chain), with test comment clarifying this is contract alignment only |
| MVC audit dependency handling | Remove interceptor/security import in tests; add missing `@MockBean` dependencies | Removing imports weakens test realism; adding mocks keeps runtime wiring intact while stabilizing test context | Keep existing `@Import(SecurityConfig...)` and add missing `AdminAuditService` mock(s) in impacted MVC tests |
| Frontend flag mocking strategy | Full inline object mock; partial module mock (`importActual` + overrides) | Full mock drifts when flags module exports grow; partial mock is slightly more verbose but resilient | Prefer partial mock pattern so new flag exports (e.g., `adminDashboardEnabled`) do not break unrelated tests |

## Data Flow

No production data flow changes. Only test bootstrapping/assertion flow changes:

    Test runner
       ├─ Backend MVC tests → load SecurityConfig + interceptor deps mocked → assert current rejection/status contract
       └─ Frontend Vitest → load flags module (partial mock) + service mocks → render App routes and assert payment flow

## File Changes

| File | Action | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `backend/src/test/java/com/eltano/ecommerce/orders/api/OrderDraftControllerTest.java` | Modify | Align `adminEndpointsRemainProtectedInMvpScope` expected status to current security contract (CSRF/auth precedence) and add explanatory assertion comment. |
| `backend/src/test/java/com/eltano/ecommerce/orders/api/MercadoPagoWebhookControllerTest.java` | Modify | Add `@MockBean AdminAuditService` so MVC context initializes with globally registered admin audit interceptor dependencies. |
| `frontend/src/app/App.payment.test.tsx` | Modify | Replace brittle full mock of `../shared/config/flags` with module-shape-consistent partial mock that preserves real exports and ensures required flags are set for the test scenario. |

## Interfaces / Contracts

No runtime interfaces or API contracts change.

Test contract updates only:
- Admin unauthenticated write-path test expectations must reflect current security filter/interceptor ordering.
- MVC tests importing `SecurityConfig` must provide required audit-service dependency mocks.
- Frontend tests mocking route flags must retain export compatibility with `frontend/src/shared/config/flags.ts`.

## Testing Strategy

| Layer | What to Test | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| Unit/Test-utils | N/A (no new units) | No new units required. |
| Integration (backend MVC) | Context boot + status assertions for targeted controllers | Run targeted JUnit classes and verify startup succeeds and adjusted assertions pass. |
| Integration (frontend component/app) | Payment app flow with route flags loaded via stable mock shape | Run targeted Vitest file and ensure no module export errors and existing scenario assertions pass. |
| E2E | None | Not required; no runtime behavior change. |

## Migration / Rollout

No migration required. This is test-only cleanup. Rollout is a single PR with only test-file diffs.

